OOP
- one of programming paradigms
- other programming paradigms include functional, procedural, imperative and declarative programming.
- allows to model data and applications that act on that data

Components of OOP
1) Abstraction
- idea of showing only the essential features of the system to user
2) Encapsulation
- grouping similar data and methods together inside a class
3) Inheritance
- child class inherits the variables and methods of parent class
4) Polymorphism
- Overloading , Overriding, Implementing Interface, Implementing Abstract Classes
-method overloading : having same method name but different method parameter or number (return type doesnt matter)
- ex  ) System.println();

